Instructions to build glint_dump_regs:
-------------------------------------

Please do the following to build glint_dump_regs:

- edit the "XC" path (without concluding slash) in Makefile 
- do "make clean; make" to compile glint_dump_regs

There are two configuration files for reading and writing registers of GLINT:
- read_regs.dat (for reading registers)
- write_regs.dat (for writing registers)

The syntax is delared in the files themselves. You have to know that
there must not be any white spaces neither between "#" and a command
like "reg", "dacreg", "echo", "echon" nor in a string. This is bad
parsing, I know. I have to fix that soon.

When you read or write registers, you get the logfiles
"/tmp/write_regs.log" and "/tmp/read_regs.log".

Have fun!

--
